entry.title: [FSA] Fix the usages of `AsValue()`
entry.content:
This CL fixes two parts:



(1) When a grant is revoked, a grant object should be removed only if

the revoked type (read or write) is the only type; if the grant object

has both read and write access, only the key should be removed from

the grant object rather than removing the entire grant object.



(2) Do not record the opposite type key within `AsValue()`. Currently,

`AsValue()` records the opposite grant type (read, write), but this is

inconsistent in several use cases, in which the opposite type is

recorded by the caller of this method. Also, it incorrectly checks for

`HasExtendedPermission()`, which would only update for extended grants

but not for dormant/shadow grants. Furthermore, this adds unnecessary

latency, as it checks PWA status for a given origin, while iterating

through files for a single origin (i.e. `GetGrantedObjects()`).

entry.title: Pass --disable-field-trial-config to tests that need it.
entry.content:
Affected tests already run without the testing config applied,

so this CL makes it explicit.



Context: Browser tests that use ScopedFeatureList and pass

params presently cause the field trial testing config to be

entirely disabled. (details: crbug.com/1491463#c8)

We plan to fix this, but some existing tests rely on this

(fail with the testing config). This CL annotates those

tests explicitly by making them specify the flag for that.



Once all the CLs updating such tests land (sharded via git

cl split), the following CL to make ScopedFeatureList not

disable the testing config can land:

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4935093



As many tests are affected, it will be up to their owners

to do any necessary follow up if the tests should be made to

pass with the testing config (per the comments this CL adds).



Note: I did a best effort to have the new flag only apply to the

subset of tests that needed it when it was a single or a small

number of tests that were affected, by introducing subclasses

for the affected tests. In other cases, where lots of tests in

the same file fail, the flag is added to the original test class.



Note: The --disable-field-trial-config flag is passed simply

by name intentionally, to avoid additional complexity from

depending on components/variations and includes to reference

the existing constant for it. The name is unlikely to change and

this way, we need less complex code to add this to the tests.



This CL was uploaded by git cl split.



R=courtneywong@chromium.org

entry.title: [Element Capture][Token] Define RestrictionTarget
entry.content:
Whereas CropTarget tokens are used as input to cropTo(),

as part of the Region Capture API

(https://www.w3.org/TR/mediacapture-region/),

RestrictionTarget tokens will be used as input restrictTo(),

as part of the Element Capture API

(https://screen-share.github.io/element-capture/).



By having two separate tokens, we ensure that minting documents

can control which capability - if any - they pass on to

cross-origin documents (whether to crop or restrict).



Upcoming CLs will round up the work:

1. Modify MediaDevicesDispatcherHost to mint the tokens.

2. Make RestrictionTarget tokens Serializable.

3. Define restrictTo() and hook it up to Viz.

4. Add end-to-end tests.

entry.title: Update TransitionalURLLoaderFactoryOwner to allow trusted params
entry.content:
CRD uses a TransitionalURLLoaderFactoryOwner instance to create

SharedURLLoaders for our host agent and utilities. We rely on this

class because our code runs outside of the browsers and does not

have access to a Mojo service instance.



This has been working fine up until we had the need to pass

trusted_params to the URLLoader. The issue is that when we do this,

the CorsURLLoader will reject the request because the 'is_trusted'

param is false.



Given that our code runs outside of the browser and it seems like

the is very little usage of this class beyond //remoting (it looks

like webdriver might be the only other caller), I would like to

pass a c'tor flag to indicate whether the Transi...Owner instance

is running in a trusted context.

entry.title: Group Network Isolation Key by joining origin
entry.content:
Right now during the interest group update process, all the interest

groups of an owner are using the same network isolation key(NIK). To

improve the privacy from NIK perspective, and also considering network

performance, we are changing the strategy that different storage

interest groups with same joining origin from all the owners can use

the same NIK.



Implementation steps:

1. For each storage interest group during the update process, it will

check if it can find isolation information with its joining origin. If

not it will create a new isolation information and put it into the map

with joining origin as the key.

2. After all the owners are updated and the queue is empty, it will

also clear the whole map.



This feature is controlled by kGroupNIKByJoiningOriginPerOwner and is

set to disabled by default.

entry.title: Phone Hub: Retry generating attestation certificates.
entry.content:
Previously we attempted to generate an attestation certificate at

the start of the Chrome session and only generate a new certificate

when it's up for rotation after 24 hours. This change triggers

an attempt to create a new certificate when the device gets internet

access if we don't have a valid one yet. It also notifies Phone Hub

when a new certificate has been generated so it can be sent to the phone

immediately if already connected.



Change-Id: I36011b2ec93e17aad2c772e5f1cb16d5d4aee192

Bug: b/300703078

Test: Verified that Phone Hub connects and works properly with the new flag enabled and disabled. Confirmed that it retries generating certs when the flag is on.

entry.title: Fix PageImageServiceQueue when pending chains into cached.
entry.content:
When an outstanding request finishes, we launch the next pending

request by calling #getSalientImageUrl again. But when that call hits

the cache, we stop polling from mQueuedRequests, while our outstanding

request count drops. This eventually orphans requests.



To fix this, we simply loop when completing an outstanding request,

until we're full on outstanding requests again.



Minor refactors also bundled into this change:

* Switch from List to int to count outstanding requests. We were

incurring O(n) to remove the request, but never using the List aspect.

* Reworked tests to primarily use ArgumentCaptor.

entry.title: CheckSecurity=ReturnValue should not re-attach a v8::Context
entry.content:
When we generate bindings for CheckSecurity=ReturnValue, we use

ToScriptState() to get a ScriptState* from the associated

LocalFrame*. If the LocalFrame is in the process of being detached

and has already detached its v8::Context, ToScriptState() will

reattach the v8::Context and WindowProxy.



This adds an early-exit when Frame::IsAttached() is false, to ensure

that we safely avoid re-attach.

demonstrates a crash because of this behavior.

entry.title: Use stronger token encryption for oauth2 token
entry.content:
This switches the oauth2 device token away from using

WeakEncryptWithSystemSalt, to the not-Weak version. It does this by

creating a new "v2" pref for storing the new formatted token.



In the store code it will always use the strong encryption and the v2

pref but to preserve the ability to read the old tokens the load code

will try to use both prefs (first v2, then falling back to the original

if that doesn't exist).
